<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-3784] TimeWindows#windowsFor misidentifies some windows if TimeWindows#advanceBy is used</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-3784</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using a time window of size 6 minutes with a 5 minute advanceBy results in some of the timestamped data being inserted into the previous overlapping window even though the event&apos;s timestamp &amp;gt; that window&apos;s end time. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fault lies in TimeWindows#windowsFor which does not check that all the windows it&apos;s adding have an endTime &amp;gt; event&apos;s timestamp. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
